@JanThomas118 

> Please correct me if i am missing something.

You're right that files with the old UID will become unavailable to the new container process, but you can fix this by using this volume option: `U, chown: true or false (default if unspecified: false). Recursively change the owner and group of the source volume based on the UID and GID of the container.` (quote from the man of `podman-run`).
